        "term": "Renaissance",
        "pronunciation": "/ˈrenəˌsäns/",
        "definition": "A period of cultural, artistic, and intellectual revival in Europe from the 14th to 17th century, marking the transition from medieval to modern times.",
        "spokenDefinition": "The Renaissance was an amazing time in European history, roughly from the 1300s to the 1600s, when art, science, and learning exploded after the darker medieval period. The word Renaissance literally means 'rebirth' in French, because it felt like civilization was being reborn.",
